' Debug-cache regression: child shared between parentA and parentB.
' Two distinct debug records — content matches nothing in extraA or extraB,
' so dedup never collapses across siblings; the bug surfaces purely because
' the shared child's cached brkCodes assume different sibling-prefix lengths
' between parentA's compile and parentB's compile.
PUB run(value) | counter
  counter := 0
  debug("shared first: value=", uhex_(value))
  repeat 2
    counter += 1
    debug("shared loop: counter=", udec_(counter))
